  <title>Math Operators in Scripting</title>

  <section>
    <title>Objective and Overview</title>

    <para>The objective of this reference article is to inform GMAT users of
    the Math Operators available to them and their syntax in scripting.</para>

    <para>(i.e. GMAT MyVar = 5 + 6 * sqrt(4))</para>

    <para>All examples assume variables and arrays, MyVar* and MyArr*, have
    already been created.</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Addition</title>

    <para>GMAT MyVar = 4 + 5;</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Subtraction</title>

    <para>GMAT MyVar = 3 - 1;</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Division</title>

    <para>GMAT MyVar = 8 / 2;</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Multiplication</title>

    <para>GMAT MyVar = 12 * 2;</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Exponentiation</title>

    <para>GMAT MyVar = 2 ^ 2;</para>
  </section>

